int decode_month(char* newn)
{
	
	char s[4];
	
	s[0]=tolower(newn[3]);
	s[1]=tolower(newn[4]);
	s[2]=tolower(newn[5]);
	s[3]='\0';
	//cout<<s<<endl;
	
	string montharr[12] =  {"jan","feb","mar","apr","may","jun","jul","aug","sep","oct","nov","dec"};
	int monthi;
	for(int i=0;i<12;i++)
	{
		if(!strcmp(s,montharr[i].c_str()))
		 {
		 	monthi = i + 1;
		 	break;
		 }
	}
	//cout<<monthi<<endl;
	return monthi;
}

int decode_day(char* newn)
{
	int date = (newn[0]-'0')*10 + (newn[1]-'0');
	return date;
}

int decode_year(char* newn)
{
	int year = (newn[7]-'0')*1000 + (newn[8]-'0')*100 + (newn[9]-'0')*10 + (newn[10]-'0');
	if(year%400==0)
	 return 1;
	else
	{
		if((year%4==0)&&(year%100!=0))
		 return 1;
	}
	return 0;
}

int Decimal_days(int* date)
{
	int montharr[12] = {31,28,31,30,31,30,31,31,30,31,30,31};
	montharr[1] += date[2];

	for(int i=0;i<date[1]-1;i++)
	{
		decimal_days += montharr[i];
	}

}
